post.title: Rest and Spread concepts in JavaScript and how to use these
post.content:
Rest and spread are javascript programming concepts that allow developers a better way to work with arrays and objects.

Rest parameters

As the name suggests rest will provide rest parameters. Let's say you have an array.

var arr = [1,2,3,4,5,6]

And you want to get only the first value in variables while keeping the rest in another variable. This is how you will do it.

var [a, ...rest]= [1,2,3,4,5,6] //here rest can be any name
console.log(a) //1
console.log(rest) // [2,3,4,5,6]- Notice

Rest always comes in the last.

The thing to notice: rest variable will be an array.

Here the purpose is: To get the elements. And in data restructuring.

Use case: Inside a react component you can access props separately like below

const { id, name, username, ...restProps } = props;

Spread operator

Spread operator — Spreads the elements of an array into individual values and will give discreet properties. Let's consider this example.

var a = [1, 2];
var b = [3, 4];
var c = [...a,...b] // array a, b spread into discrete properties
console.log(c); // [1,2,3,4]

In the above example, spread operators spread the properties and formed a new array.

Purpose: Creating shallow copies, overriding data, rearranging data, adding up, eliminating duplicated, etc

Use Case: Creating shallow copy, merging data into a single instance, etc
